    <item>
      <title>全身扫描未能改善美国疾病预防</title>
      <link>https://www.npr.org/sections/shots-health-news/2024/06/18/nx-s1-5009259/full-body-scan-mri-prevention-cancer-screening</link>
      <description><![CDATA[名人影响者正在推广昂贵的扫描以便尽早发现疾病，但一位医生认为，美国应该专注于让每个人都得到经过验证的筛查和预防策略。]]></description>
      <guid>https://www.npr.org/sections/shots-health-news/2024/06/18/nx-s1-5009259/full-body-scan-mri-prevention-cancer-screening</guid>
      <pubDate>Tue, 18 Jun 2024 11:05:00 GMT</pubDate>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>如果人工智能如此优秀，为什么仍然需要翻译人员的工作？</title>
      <link>https://www.npr.org/sections/planet-money/2024/06/18/g-s1-4461/if-ai-is-so-good-why-are-there-still-so-many-jobs-for-translators</link>
      <description><![CDATA[外语机器翻译已经流行了一段时间。然而，人工翻译仍然供不应求。为什么人工智能没有取代这些工作？即使没有，它又是如何重塑这些工作的？]]></description>
      <guid>https://www.npr.org/sections/planet-money/2024/06/18/g-s1-4461/if-ai-is-so-good-why-are-there-still-so-many-jobs-for-translators</guid>
      <pubDate>Tue, 18 Jun 2024 10:30:00 GMT</pubDate>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>为什么极端高温在美国不被视为灾难？</title>
      <link>https://www.npr.org/2024/06/18/nx-s1-5003785/extreme-heat-disaster-fema-climate</link>
      <description><![CDATA[联邦紧急事务管理局从未对致命或破坏性的极端高温做出过反应。环保组织和工会要求改变这一现状。]]></description>
      <guid>https://www.npr.org/2024/06/18/nx-s1-5003785/extreme-heat-disaster-fema-climate</guid>
      <pubDate>Tue, 18 Jun 2024 09:30:00 GMT</pubDate>
    </item>
